nl.uva.se.imppipes

Class StartFilter<I>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • nl.uva.se.imppipes.Filter<I,I>
        • nl.uva.se.imppipes.StartFilter<I>
  • Type Parameters:
    I - the type of Objects in the List of elements this StartFilter should have processed
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Runnable

    public class StartFilter<I>
extends Filter<I,I>
    A special type of Filter that has all elements in a List processed by a chain of FilterScalers following this StartFilter.
    Author:
    FT_7

      • StartFilter

        public StartFilter(java.util.List<I> inputList,
                   FilterScaler<I,? extends java.lang.Object> next,
                   java.lang.Object theMonitor)
        Constructor for Objects of class StartFilter.
        Parameters:
        inputList - the List of Objects to be processed by the FilterScalers following this StartFilter
        next - the FilterScaler which queue this StartFilter should add the elements of inputList to
        theMonitor - an Object to synchronize stopping the chain of FilterScalers following this StartFilter on when necessary. Before getting the result of filtering the elements of inputList from the FilterScaler ending the chain of FilterScalers started by this StartFilter, a caller should wait to be notified by theMonitor

    • Method Detail

      • clone

        public StartFilter<I> clone()
        Description copied from class: Filter
        Returns a Filter of the same type as this Filter, processing input from the same queue and adding the results to the same FilterScaler. N.B. This method can be inconsistent with Object.equals(java.lang.Object) and Object.hashCode().
        Specified by:
        clone in class Filter<I,I>
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - because cloning a StartFilter could cause an Object processed by this StartFilter to be processed by it's clone too and then be processed by the chain of FilterScalers following this StartFilter (and it's clone) multiple times
        See Also:
        Filter.copyNextAndQueue(Filter, Filter)

      • process

        public I process(I input)
        Description copied from class: Filter
        Processes a value. This method defines what this Filter does with each value it gets from it's queue before adding it to the next FilterScaler.
        Specified by:
        process in class Filter<I,I>
        Parameters:
        input - the value to process
        Returns:
        input, for using a StartFilter more like other Filters

      • run

        public void run()
        This method should not be called manually but is called by Thread.start() when that method is called to run this Filter. When this method is called, this StartFilter starts the next FilterScaler and immediatly calls stopeExecution() on, waits for the FilterScalers following this StartFilter to finish processing all input and notifies all Objects waiting for the monitor passed to the constructor of this class when constructing this StartFilter, to signal them the filtering has finished and the results can be obtained (from the last FilterScaler chained to this StartFilter.
        Specified by:
        run in interface java.lang.Runnable
        Overrides:
        run in class Filter<I,I>

      • isPipeStopped

        public boolean isPipeStopped()
        Returns:
        whether or not processing all input was processed by the whole chain of FilterScalers following this StartFilter

      • stopExecution

        public boolean stopExecution()
        Calls stopExecution() on the FilterScaler following this StartFilter, to stop the whole chain of FilterScalers.
        Overrides:
        stopExecution in class Filter<I,I>
        Returns:
        true when this Filter has finished running
